<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 5:55AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Reduced Visibility this Morning...
Patchy fog has developed this morning within the valleys of
Southwest Montana. Localized dense fog is possible in a few areas,
mainly near rivers. Motorist should be prepared for reduced
visibilities to as low as one quarter of a mile in the densest
fog. Slow down, allow extra traveling distances between vehicles,
and use low beam headlights when traveling through fog.</description>
